<br>
Pets not zoning is ok for the most part from a PvE standpoint, but I think PvP mages get a bit of a shaft when it comes to zoning.  I have no PvP experience though.  Also, for zones designed to be zone in and fight, such as PoF(not that I'd zone a pet into PoF anyway, but..), it's a slightly unfair penalty<br>
<br>
However, losing your pet when you go linkdead has never been fair. no other class suffers as much as magicians in this regard, except illusioned enchanters on some occaisions.  Other pet classes, such as necromancers, suffer from this as well, but by far the most helpless class upon logging in after a linkdeath is a magician.<br>
<br>
Magicians can place themselves in a position where they are way overpowered, go linkdead, and come back with gate or die as the only reasonable options. <p><font face = "Arial" color=0000EE><center><b>Goladus Mistrydia</b></font><br>
