Torvonnilous Server - We kill mobs too</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=thedwellerindarkness>thedwellerindarkness</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mage</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(1/25/02 6:35:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   pet zoning issue</span><hr size=1> First of all, I don't think this is an ability that we NEED. Truthfully I never gave it much thought after the first couple weeks of starting EQ, and we've certainly done without it long enough. However, it's not a matter of necessity, it's really a matter of us as a pet class taking a disadvantage that other non-pet classes don't have to deal with. Verant has made up thier mind that we are about as powerful as we will ever get, based on the fact that in ideal situations we are very powerful with pets. All of our other spells are balanced against us having a pet up. When we zone, and have no pet, we are at a disadvantage of the same magnitude as a tank with no armor, or a shammy completely buffless. It may only take a minute or 2 to recast a pet, a little longer if you summon as much gear for them as I tend to, but no one else has to rebuff when they zone.<br>
<br>
Secondly, I don't see a thing unbalancing about mage pets zoning.  If a mage wants to trick out his pet with all sorts of gear and nice weapons, he can do that now and sit in 1 zone all day, and if he's careful, not lose the pet.  He could even find a safe corner, and not bother to log that night, keeping the pet for the next day. In my mind the mage making an uber pet just because he zone with it isn't much different.  Besides, there are plenty of ways to lose a pet that you've given stuff to whether they zone with you or not.<br>
<br>
Lastly, on the technical issue, I'm not suggesting that it would be easy for them to implement zoning pets, I'm just saying it's not impossible.  Frankly, I could care less how hard it would be for them to code it. They have changed enough stuff that &quot;couldn't work&quot; to continue to use that excuse. Maybe I don't understand programming well enough to understand why a pet can't be saved to our char as a specialized container. If it's a matter of data space, I would gladly give up a general inventory slot (that would normally allow me to hold a 10 slot bag), and have 10 slots worth of data that I &quot;fill&quot; by handing them to Jibaner, and that gets saved with me when I zone. These items then get &quot;given&quot; to my pet on the other side of the zone. If they will soon be able to make players into merchants, they can't think of a way to make pets zone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uylaine76.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ylaine76</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 303<br> <font color=#333333>(1/25/02 9:17:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=39.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: pet zoning issue</span><hr size=1> Yeah I understand the points, but once again <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  The pets that are allowed to zone are of no real power, since beastlords have to spend mana to rebuff<br>
